# TapAuth PAM module configuration example.
# Add the following line to your PAM service file (e.g. /etc/pam.d/system-auth
# for login, or /etc/pam.d/sudo for sudo) to enable phone-based authentication:
#
#   auth    sufficient    pam_tapauth.so
#
# For Fedora systems using authselect, create a custom profile first:
#   sudo authselect create-profile tapauth-custom -b sssd
# then edit /etc/authselect/custom/tapauth-custom/system-auth
# and apply with: sudo authselect select custom/tapauth-custom
#
# For Arch Linux, manually add the line to /etc/pam.d/system-auth.
# For Ubuntu/Debian, use: sudo pam-auth-update
